TextEng: What exactly are Lord Nasher's orders?
What be Lord Nasher's orders?
I am more concerned about how you are holding up.
Text: 당신이 어떻게 지내고 있는지가 더 걱정됩니다.

TextEng: Me more concern about you, not orders.
What do you think I should do now?
Text: 지금 제가 무엇을 해야 한다고 생각하십니까?

TextEng: What you think me should do?
Text: 너 나 뭐 해야 한다고 생각해?

TextEng: I have some questions about this mission.
Text: 이 임무에 대해 몇 가지 질문이 있습니다.

TextEng: Me has questions about mission.
How are you feeling? This must be a terrible strain.
How you feel? This all big headache, no?
Text: 기분 어때? 이거 다 머리 아픈 일이지, 그치?

TextEng: Do you have any advice for me?
You haves advice, maybe?
You want to find this cult badly, do you?
Text: 이 사교를 정말 찾고 싶으신 거군요?

TextEng: You wants to find cult badly, huh?
Text: 너 사교 정말 찾고 싶은 거지, 응?

TextEng: I'll go now.
Me go now.
What are you and Aarin Gend going to be doing here while I search?
Text: 제가 수색하는 동안 당신과 아린 겐드는 여기서 무엇을 하실 겁니까?

TextEng: What you and spymaster doing here while me searches?
Text: 나 찾는 동안 너랑 첩보장 여기서 뭐 해?

TextEng: How do you propose I look for this cult?
How does I looks for cult?
What should I do if I discover something?
What me do if I finds something out?
Why are we not searching more in Neverwinter?
Text: 왜 네버윈터에서 더 수색하지 않는 겁니까?

TextEng: Why we not searching more in city?
Text: 왜 우리 도시에서 더 안 찾아?

TextEng: Just what do we know about this cult?
Text: 이 사교에 대해 정확히 무엇을 알고 있습니까?

TextEng: What we knows about cult, anyway?
Text: 우리 사교에 대해 뭐 알아, 어쨌든?

TextEng: I want to ask something else.
Me has other question.
I have located some information about the cult.
Me find out stuff about cult.
That sounds like a dangerous task.
Enter tower? It sound mighty dangerous.
Can I expect some help? Will you be coming with me?
Text: 도움을 기대해도 됩니까? 저와 함께 오실 건가요?

TextEng: Me get help? You coming, too?
How will I get into the tower?
How me get into tower? You know?
Text: 나 탑에 어떻게 들어가? 너 알아?

TextEng: I'll do my best.
Me go now, then.
What do you mean? What plans?
What you mean? What you plan?
You look tired. Have you not been sleeping well?
Text: 피곤해 보이시는군요. 잠을 잘 못 주무시나요?

TextEng: You looks tired. You not sleeps good?
Text: 너 피곤해 보여. 잠 잘 못 자?

TextEng: Aarin says you have been having disturbing dreams.
Text: 아린이 당신이 불안한 꿈을 꾸고 있다고 하더군요.

TextEng: Aarin say you haves bad dreams.
Text: 아린이 너 나쁜 꿈 꾼다고 해.

TextEng: You said I should ask you how you became a paladin.
Text: 당신이 어떻게 성기사가 되었는지 물어보라고 하셨죠.

TextEng: You say me should ask how you become paladin.
Text: 너 나한테 어떻게 성기사 됐는지 물어보라고 했어.

TextEng: You seem angry. Is something wrong?
You looks angry. Is something wrong?
Aarin mentioned that you've been very short of temper.
Text: 아린이 당신이 요즘 매우 성질이 급하다고 하더군요.

TextEng: Aarin say you very angry all the time.
Text: 아린이 너 맨날 엄청 화낸다고 해.

TextEng: Everyone can make a mistake, Aribeth, even for the best reasons.
Text: 누구나 실수할 수 있습니다, 아리베스. 최선의 이유에서라도요.

TextEng: Fenthick was a fool to follow his duty so blindly.
Text: 펜딕은 의무를 맹목적으로 따르느라 바보가 되었습니다.

TextEng: It is very sad, what happened to him. I am sorry for your loss.
Text: 그에게 일어난 일은 매우 슬픕니다. 당신의 상실에 애도를 표합니다.

TextEng: Don't be so naive. Not everyone is as caught up in duty and goodness as you are.
Text: 그렇게 순진하지 마십시오. 모두가 당신처럼 의무와 선에 사로잡힌 건 아닙니다.

TextEng: Even a paladin has a heart, Aribeth... you can't be the avatar of justice all the time.
Text: 성기사도 마음이 있습니다, 아리베스... 항상 정의의 화신일 수는 없어요.

TextEng: I don't really have anything to say about that.
Text: 그것에 대해 특별히 할 말이 없습니다.

TextEng: All can makes mistake, even me knows that.
Fenthick was dummy to only see duty.
Yes, is all very sad. Me sorry.
Pfft. You naive. Nobody thinks duty everything like you.
Text: 흥. 너 순진해. 아무도 너처럼 의무가 전부라고 안 생각해.

TextEng: You haves heart, Aribeth... you not be perfect.
Text: 너도 마음 있어, 아리베스... 너 완벽하지 않아.

TextEng: Me not haves anything to say 'bout that.
Text: 나 그것에 대해 말할 거 없어.

TextEng: Don't let feelings blind you to the truth about Fenthick, Aribeth.
Text: 감정이 펜딕에 대한 진실을 가리지 못하게 하세요, 아리베스.

TextEng: You feelings is blinding you 'bout Fenthick, Aribeth.
Text: 너 감정이 펜딕에 대해 장님 만들어, 아리베스.

TextEng: <StartCheck>[Persuade]</Start> No, go on. Tell me what you were going to say.
<StartCheck>[Persuade]</Start> No, you speak. Tells me what you going to say.
Text: <StartCheck>[설득]</Start> 아니, 너 말해. 하려던 말 나한테 해.

TextEng: Just make sure this doesn't come up again.
Text: 이런 일이 다시 생기지 않게 확실히 하세요.

TextEng: You makes sure this don't come up again, then.
Text: 너 이거 다시 안 나오게 확실히 해, 그럼.

TextEng: Yes, it is. You should pull yourself together.
No, you're being too hard on yourself, Aribeth.
It is never wrong to question. What's important are your answers.
Text: 질문하는 것은 잘못이 아닙니다. 중요한 건 당신의 답입니다.

TextEng: I can't answer that for you, Aribeth.
Text: 제가 당신을 위해 답할 수 없습니다, 아리베스.

TextEng: Yes. You shoulds get head together.
You be too hard on youself.
Is not wrong to ask. What answer is, is important.
Text: 질문하는 거 잘못 아니야. 답이 중요한 거야.

TextEng: Me cannot answer for you, Miss Aribeth.
Text: 나 너를 위해 답 못 해, 아리베스 아가씨.

TextEng: No, he didn't.
<StartCheck>[Lie]</Start> Yes, he did, actually.
No, he no tell me anything.
<StartCheck>[Lie]</Start> Yes, he dids.
No, it's not surprising at all.
These dreams are disturbing enough to keep you from sleep?
Text: 이 꿈들이 잠을 못 잘 만큼 불안합니까?

TextEng: What sorts of things do the servants claim you say?
Perhaps you've gone mad. Completely cracked.
Text: 아마도 미쳐버린 거겠죠. 완전히 정신이 나갔어요.

TextEng: No, is no surprise.
Dreams is disturbing and you no sleep?
What servants say you speak in sleep?
Text: 하인들이 너 자면서 뭐라고 말한다고 해?

TextEng: Maybe you gone mad, a crazy woman.
You don't sound very convinced.
You no sounds convinced.
<StartCheck>[Persuade]</Start> Why don't you tell me about these dreams? Maybe it will help.
Text: <StartCheck>[설득]</Start> 이 꿈들에 대해 말씀해주시지 않겠습니까? 도움이 될 수도 있습니다.

TextEng: <StartCheck>[Persuade]</Start> Why don't you tell me about these dreams? Maybe it will help.
Text: <StartCheck>[설득]</Start> 이 꿈들에 대해 말씀해주시지 않겠습니까? 도움이 될 수도 있습니다.

TextEng: Have you considered that maybe it's more serious than that?
Text: 그것보다 더 심각한 걸 수도 있다고 생각해보셨습니까?

TextEng: <StartCheck>[Persuade]</Start> Tell me 'bout dreams. Maybe it help.
Text: <StartCheck>[설득]</Start> 꿈에 대해 말해. 도움 될 수도 있어.

TextEng: <StartCheck>[Persuade]</Start> Tell me 'bout dreams. Maybe it help.
Text: <StartCheck>[설득]</Start> 꿈에 대해 말해. 도움 될 수도 있어.

TextEng: You think maybes it more serious?
Text: 너 아마 더 심각한 거라고 생각해?

TextEng: That's understandable. They would frighten me, as well.
Obviously something is seriously wrong with you.
It is only fears and worries dredged up by your mind, Aribeth.
Text: 그건 단지 당신의 마음이 끌어올린 두려움과 걱정일 뿐입니다, 아리베스.

TextEng: I don't know what to say about that.
Text: 그것에 대해 뭐라고 말해야 할지 모르겠습니다.

TextEng: Is okay. Me would be scared, too.
Something big wrong with you, maybe.
Text: 너한테 뭔가 큰 문제 있는 거 같아.

TextEng: It only you mind full of fear and worry, me think.
Text: 그냥 너 마음에 두려움이랑 걱정 가득한 거야, 나 생각엔.

TextEng: Me not know what to say.
Perhaps I'm wrong, then. I'm sorry.
Deny it if you wish, Aribeth, it's not natural.
Text: 부정하고 싶으면 하세요, 아리베스. 자연스럽지 않습니다.

TextEng: I'm no fool, Aribeth... and neither should you be!
Text: 저는 바보가 아닙니다, 아리베스... 당신도 그래서는 안 됩니다!

TextEng: Maybe me wrong. Me sorry.
You say it wrong if you likes... it not normal.
Text: 너 틀렸다고 말하고 싶으면 해... 정상 아니야.

TextEng: Me no fool. You should no be fool, neither.
Text: 나 바보 아니야. 너도 바보 되면 안 돼.

TextEng: No, I want to hear it.
I'll let you know if I get bored, don't worry.
Maybe some other time, then.
No, me wants to hear it.
Me let you know if I gets bored, you no worry.
Okay, me hears later.
That doesn't sound like you at all.
How did you become a paladin after that?
Okay, getting bored now...
That no sound like you.
How you be paladin after that?
Okay, me gettings bored...
Who was the man who saved you?
The man who saved you... that was Tyr?
You're right, this is a long story.
Who man that save you?
Man who save you... is Tyr?
You is right, is long story.
No, I'm only joking.
Yes, maybe I'll hear this later.
No, me just joke.
Yes, me hear later.
What happened then?
You became a cleric, then, like Fenthick?
So you think Tyr, himself, commanded you to worship him?
Text: 그래서 티르가 직접 자신을 섬기라고 명령했다고 생각하십니까?

TextEng: What happen then?
You becomes cleric? Like Fenthick?
So you thinks Tyr tell you to worships him?
Text: 그래서 너 티르가 자기 섬기라고 말했다고 생각해?

TextEng: I'm sorry, I didn't mean to sadden you.
So were those dreams like the ones you have now?
Text: 그럼 그 꿈들이 지금 꾸는 꿈들과 비슷했습니까?

TextEng: You're not going to cry again, are you?
Okay, story over. Let's talk about something else.
Me sorry... not mean to make you sad.
Text: 나 미안해... 슬프게 하려던 거 아니야.

TextEng: Those dreams like dreams now?
You not goings to cry again, me hope.
Okay, story is done. We talk 'bout something else.
Text: 알았어, 이야기 끝. 우리 다른 얘기해.

TextEng: What has changed?
What change?
I do.
I don't need another friend.
Whoa... slow down there, lady!
Does this mean we can go to bed soon?
Text: 이게 곧 잠자리에 갈 수 있다는 뜻입니까?

TextEng: Me does.
Me need no more friends.
Whoa! You be very forward!
Uhh... this mean we goes to bed soon?
Text: 어... 이거 우리 곧 자러 간다는 뜻이야?

TextEng: But Fenthick was involved in the deaths of thousands of people!
Text: 하지만 펜딕은 수천 명의 죽음에 연루되었습니다!

TextEng: Perhaps it's Fenthick you should be angry at.
And what should have happened, do you think?
Maybe you should be angry.
I don't like hearing you talk like this.
Text: 이런 식으로 말하는 걸 듣고 싶지 않습니다.

TextEng: But Fenthick help kill many people!
Text: 하지만 펜딕이 많은 사람 죽이는 거 도왔어!

TextEng: Maybe you shoulds be mad at Fenthick.
What you thinks should have happen?
Maybe is okay you are angry.
Me no like hearing you speaks like this.
Text: 나 너 이렇게 말하는 거 듣는 거 싫어.

TextEng: You sound as if you're losing your faith.
What brought this on, all of a sudden?
Don't talk like that! Stop it, this isn't like you!
Text: 그렇게 말하지 마세요! 그만하세요, 이건 당신답지 않아요!

TextEng: Finally I think you're seeing the light!
You sounds like you loses faith.
Why you act like this now?
You no talk like that! This not you!
Text: 그렇게 말하지 마! 이건 너답지 않아!

TextEng: Finally me thinks you sees the light!
Text: 마침내 나 너 진실 본다고 생각해!

TextEng: The dreams have gotten worse?
This is bad. Perhaps we should return to Neverwinter.
Text: 이건 안 좋습니다. 네버윈터로 돌아가야 할지도 모르겠습니다.

TextEng: I think you really may be going mad!
I have almost had enough of your constant angst.
Dreams worse now?
This bad. We shoulds go to Neverwinter.
Text: 이거 나빠. 우리 네버윈터로 가야 해.

TextEng: Me thinks you go mad!
Me have almost enough of you bellyacheing.
Text: 나 너 계속 불평하는 거 거의 질려.

TextEng: I promise.
I can't promise that, Aribeth.
I don't think that will help you.
Text: 그게 도움이 될 것 같지 않습니다.

TextEng: You are mad!
Me promise.
Me can no promise that!
I no think this helps you, Aribeth.
Text: 나 이거 너 도움 안 된다고 생각해, 아리베스.

TextEng: You is mad!
What do you mean?
Very well, I will take it.
No, I don't want it.
What you mean?
Okay, me take it.
No, me not want it.
Me not finds anything yet.
Nothing yet.
<StartAction>Show her the letter to Vardoc.</Start>
<StartAction>Show her the Charwood cultist's journal.</Start>
<StartAction>Show her Relmar's journal.</Start>
Me keeps on looking.
I shall continue the search.
<StartAction>Show her the letter to Neva.</Start>
<StartAction>Show her the letter to Solomon.</Start>
<StartAction>Show her Ganon's journal.</Start>
No other stuffs yet.
Nothing else, no.
